The number of graduates from universities in Beijing in 2022 is expected to reach 268,000 - Xinhua News Agency. According to a recent video conference on the employment and entrepreneurship of 2022 college graduates in Beijing, which was jointly held by the Beijing Municipal Education Commission and the Beijing Human Resources and Social Security Bureau, it is estimated that there will be 26.8 thousand college graduates in the Beijing area in 2022, an increase of 16,000 compared to the previous year. The relevant person in charge of the Beijing Human Resources and Social Security Bureau stated that they will deploy the employment work for college graduates in Beijing from aspects such as enhancing matching supply and demand, strengthening policy support, expanding employment channels, ensuring assistance for difficult families, supporting innovation and entrepreneurship, and improving service efficiency. The reporter learned that the Beijing Human Resources and Social Security Bureau will build a practical platform, increase job supply, actively contact 40 college graduate work experience bases, visit employers, integrate demand information and job information; they will focus on "six batches", that is, expanding the recruitment of a batch of public institutions, expanding the recruitment of a batch of state-owned enterprises, expanding the recruitment of a batch of grassroots projects, expanding the enlistment of a batch, expanding the employment of a batch of trainees and interns, and expanding the employment of a batch of entrepreneurs; they will implement the "one-life one-policy" dynamic management, recommend at least 5 job information for each graduate, and ensure that 100% of graduates from families with employment willingness receive assistance, etc.
